{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"SMOKE TEST (published 0.6.0): installed via 'pipx install nava-rebar[mcp]==0.6.0 --force' (rebar + rebar-mcp shims present). Probed the SHIPPED pipx binary (REBAR=pipx shim) against an explicitly 'rebar init'-ed isolated temp store (PROBE_LIVE=1 + REBAR_ROOT=tmp; store verified unchanged after).\n\nRESULT: 138 passed, 3 failed. All 3 failures are STALE PROBE-SCRIPT expectations, NOT 0.6.0 defects:\n  (1) line 146 'edit multi-field' uses 'edit --tags', which the engine intentionally removed (CLAUDE.md: --tags is not an edit field; use --set-tags/--add-tag/--remove-tag). Command errors by design.\n  (2) line 147 'edit priority persisted' is collateral of (1): --priority=3 rode on the same multi-field edit that failed on --tags, so priority stayed at its prior value.\n  (3) line 276 'show and list identical key sets': show returns comments+description (detail view); list omits them by design (summary view). Probe's identical-keyset assumption is wrong.\n\nConclusion: the published artifact installs and every real CLI command works. The 3 failures are pre-existing probe drift (predate 0.6.0). Filing as discovered follow-up."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782767101485871001,"uuid":"613e17a6-5809-4444-9b22-7bdbb53332ea"}